<plot>Inzeyen' - Malina is the feature film about modern Russia, human relations and the discrepancy of Russian soul. It is a tractate on emptiness with elements of absurdity. There are no much dialogues, but it is full of humor and light grief. It consists of 8 short independent stories, which are connected by one character - Alexey Pankratov, Head of Cultural Department of Inza district. It is a drama of a young talented man, who aspires to be pulled out from the world of a surrounding reality. He tries to fill his ordinary provincial life with spiritual events. Alexey is an admirer of Marc Chagall and even tries to paint like him. He is a close friend of well-known naive painter Katya Medvedeva, played by herself. That is she tells Alexey: "Just close your eyes, Lesha, and repeat this magic word: IN-ZE-YEN'..." He closes his eyes and hears a peal in that magic darkness. Each hero of all 8 film novellas helps to discover an interesting deep personality of Alexey. This film is for for all your senses</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?268116</url></doc>
